com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functions

Interface Fn1<A,B>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - The argument type
    B - The result type
    All Superinterfaces:
    Function<A,B>, Functor<B>, Profunctor<A,B>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CheckedFn1<A,B>, Fn2<A,B,C>, Fn3<A,B,C,D>, Predicate<A>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    All, Any, CartesianProduct, Constantly, Cycle, Drop, DropWhile, Filter, FoldLeft, FoldRight, Id, InGroupsOf, Iterate, Map, Partial2, Partial3, ReduceLeft, ReduceRight, Repeat, Reverse, ScanLeft, Take, TakeWhile, Tupler2, Unfoldr, Zip, ZipWith
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Fn1<A,B>
extends Functor<B>, Profunctor<A,B>, Function<A,B>
    A function taking a single argument. This is the core function type that all other function types extend and auto-curry with.
